def miss_val(df):
    misval = df.isnull().sum()
    miss_per = 100 * misval/len(df)
    df1 = pd.concat([misval,miss_per],axis=1)
    renamed = df1.rename(columns={0:'missing_val',1:'missing %'})
    new = renamed[renamed.iloc[:,1] !=0].sort_values('missing_val',ascending=False)
    return new

def transformed_var(df,var):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))
    plt.subplot(1,2,1)
    df[var].hist()
    plt.subplot(1,2,2)
    st.probplot(df[var],dist='norm',plot=plt)
    plt.show()

Test of Normality¶

Normality:The population data sould follow normal ( by default alpha =5%) H0: pop data = Normal

H1: pop data != normal

Note: if p value >=alpha --> pop data = Normal

In [40]:
sns.distplot(df.Branch_Id)
Out[40]:
<AxesSubplot:xlabel='Branch_Id', ylabel='Density'>
In [41]:
st.shapiro(df.Branch_Id)
Out[41]:
ShapiroResult(statistic=0.9462637305259705, pvalue=0.0)

Since p value <alpha (0.05) --> reject H0.¶

Hence we can conclude that pop data of total bill does not folow normal distribution

So we can not do the parametric test. proceed for non parametric test

Test of Median H0: pop median_total bill >=25

H1:pop median_total Bill <25

test of Variance equality - Levene test¶

H0: pop1 _variance = pop2 Variance

H1: pop1 _variance != pop2 Variance

Note: if p value >= alpha--> pop variances are equal

In [52]:

LeveneResult(statistic=14.54793039374196, pvalue=0.0001370028230183985)

H0: pop_mean_tb_Se = pop_mean_tb_e ** mu_tbSe-mu_tb_e=0

H1: pop_mean_tb_Se != pop_mean_tb_e ** mu_tbm-mu_tb_e!=0

In [54]:
alpha=0.05
x1= tb_Se.mean()
x2= tb_e.mean()
s1_2= tb_Se.var()
s2_2= tb_e.var()
n1= len(tb_Se)
n2= len(tb_e)
pooled_var= ((n1-1)*s1_2+(n2-1)*s2_2)/(n1+n2-2)
std_error = np.sqrt(pooled_var*((1/n1)+(1/n2)))
t_st= (x1-x2)/std_error
t_crit = st.t.isf(alpha/2, n1+n2-2)
print(t_st, t_crit)
